Prerequisites:
ros stacks common, common_msgs, drivers_common, image_common, ros, ros_comm
See www.ros.org/wiki/Installation
If already setup:
sudo apt-get install ros-unstable-image-common ros-unstable-drivers-common

Create kinect.rosinstall
"""
- git:
    local-name: kinect
    uri: https://github.com/ros-pkg-git/kinect.git
    version: master
"""

# do installation from source
rosinstall ~/kinect_dev /opt/ros/unstable kinect.rosinstall
. ~/kinect_dev/setup.sh

If you want write access use the following in ~/kinect_dev/kinect:
git remote set-url origin git@github.com:ros-pkg-git/kinect.git

For now call `git submodule update --init --recursive` to pull in libfreenect
Patch for rosinstall coming https://code.ros.org/trac/ros/ticket/3146

# Build all of kinect stack and install dependencies
rosmake --rosdep-install kinect


To use the kinect you will have to give yourself permissions on the USB ports /dev/bus/usb/*

If you want to write back to ros-pkg-git/libfreenect
roscd freenect/libfreenect && git remote set-url git@github.com:ros-pkg-git/libfreenect.git

Note: When committing to ros-pkg-git/libfreenect always:
1) sign your commits.  See http://openkinect.org/wiki/Contributing_Code#Sign_your_work
2) We default to the ros branch, not in master.  There's a lot going on in the master branch, we'll leave it available for upstream integration.  